% Write `pdd/commands/checkup_snapshot.py`, implementing the `snapshot` Click command used by `pdd checkup snapshot`.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Role & Scope
This module implements the `snapshot` Click command, which enforces snapshot policy for nondeterministic prompts. It explicitly rejects the `--review` flag with a usage error because advisory LLM passes are not supported for snapshot checks.

% Requirements
1. Implement `@click.command("snapshot")` with the existing interface: `PROMPT_FILE` argument (Path, must exist), `--project-root` (Path, default `.`), `--json` flag.
2. Wire `--review off|explain` (default `off`) using the `review_option` decorator from `pdd.commands.checkup_review_options`.
3. At the start of the command body, call `reject_review_on_snapshot(review)` from `pdd.commands.checkup_review_options` to raise `click.UsageError` when `review != "off"`, before any deterministic work begins.
4. Preserve existing behavior: call `check_snapshot_policy(prompt_file, project_root)` from `pdd.context_snapshot_policy`, emit JSON or human-readable output, exit 1 on failure.
5. JSON payload shape is unchanged: `{"passed": bool, "prompt": str, "message": str}`.
6. Import `check_snapshot_policy` from `pdd.context_snapshot_policy`.

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/commands/checkup_snapshot.py`
